  <br>
If so, then that is in direct opposition to the History Channel's <br>
program on Project Orion.  They interviewed several of the scientists <br>
involved, one even correcting the mis-belief that a nuclear detonation <br>
would vaporize anything within a few hundred meters.  <br>
They claimed that this simply wasn't true, even went so far as to<br>
say that fiberglass would suffice as pusher plate material.<br>
